WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.888
Every badge, every credential, every clearance... starts with a packet of paperwork.

00:06.938 --> 00:11.183
This is AkamaiForms. Every submission, review ready.

00:12.433 --> 00:15.812
If you run a badging office, you know this inbox.

00:15.862 --> 00:20.080
The application with fourteen attachments and the wrong form.

00:20.130 --> 00:25.189
The one that's missing a signature — which nobody notices until Thursday.

00:25.239 --> 00:30.297
The new hire who shows up to their appointment with an expired license...

00:30.347 --> 00:31.767
and has to come back.

00:31.817 --> 00:37.155
Every one of those is another email, another week, another pushed start date.

00:37.205 --> 00:41.844
And the people sorting it out are your most experienced reviewers —

00:41.894 --> 00:46.812
spending their day re-reading attachments, instead of making decisions.

00:48.062 --> 00:50.852
AkamaiForms sits in front of that inbox,

00:50.902 --> 00:54.119
and inspects every packet the moment it lands.

00:54.169 --> 00:58.095
Complete packets are cleared, and waiting in your queue.

00:58.145 --> 01:03.492
Broken packets get a fix list — a correction letter written the same minute,

01:03.542 --> 01:07.894
naming exactly what's missing. It waits in your drafts folder.

01:07.944 --> 01:11.515
Nothing is ever sent without a person approving it.

01:11.565 --> 01:15.918
And anything genuinely uncertain is flagged for your judgment.

01:15.968 --> 01:18.758
The system never guesses on your behalf.

01:20.008 --> 01:21.733
Now, put numbers on it.

01:21.783 --> 01:27.596
By hand, a packet takes about eighteen minutes of a coordinator's attention.

01:27.646 --> 01:33.151
At real loaded cost, that's eleven dollars and forty cents — per packet.

01:33.201 --> 01:36.777
Across a year... twenty-seven thousand dollars.

01:36.827 --> 01:39.786
And that's before a single resend loop.

01:39.836 --> 01:43.952
AkamaiForms does that first pass for about four cents.

01:44.002 --> 01:49.430
Ninety-six dollars a year, total. That's twenty-seven thousand dollars,

01:49.480 --> 01:54.830
and seven hundred twenty hours of reviewer attention, back every year.

01:54.880 --> 01:58.071
Your numbers will differ. The shape won't.

01:59.321 --> 02:01.242
Here's the whole picture.

02:01.292 --> 02:06.447
Your mailbox stays your mailbox — applicants don't change a thing.

02:06.497 --> 02:12.125
Inside it, a preflight inspector reads every page, typed or handwritten.

02:12.175 --> 02:17.566
It checks each packet against the rulebook your office signed off on.

02:17.616 --> 02:23.007
And before it trusts its own reading, it double-checks it — a second,

02:23.057 --> 02:26.320
independent look at every important field.

02:26.370 --> 02:32.076
Every packet lands in one of three places: cleared... fix list drafted...

02:32.126 --> 02:34.127
or set aside for a person.

02:34.177 --> 02:40.041
And every step is written into a sealed logbook you can prove months later,

02:40.091 --> 02:41.145
for any audit.

02:42.395 --> 02:48.144
This is the console your team sees. Let's look at a morning's mail.

02:49.394 --> 02:53.506
Six packets came in overnight — and they're already sorted.

02:53.556 --> 02:58.161
The queue reads top to bottom in the order your attention matters:

02:58.211 --> 03:03.450
one packet needs a person, four need fixes, and one is cleared and waiting.

03:04.700 --> 03:08.786
Start where you're needed most. On this application,

03:08.836 --> 03:14.671
the inspector read the city two different ways — so it stopped, and asked.

03:14.721 --> 03:16.897
Both readings, side by side.

03:16.947 --> 03:23.021
Hover, and you can see exactly where each one came from. A person settles it.

03:23.071 --> 03:24.373
The system waits.

03:26.700 --> 03:33.080
Next, a fix. This applicant sent a reference sheet, a photo of their license,

03:33.130 --> 03:39.344
and a document we don't recognize — but not the two forms we actually need.

03:39.394 --> 03:42.517
The findings say so in plain language.

03:42.567 --> 03:49.281
And the reply is already written — waiting in your drafts, never sent on its own.

03:49.331 --> 03:52.538
One click to copy. Review it, and send.

03:53.788 --> 03:59.686
And here's the good news story. Both forms, an ID, every rule satisfied.

03:59.736 --> 04:01.256
Cleared for review.

04:01.306 --> 04:07.452
Your reviewer starts here — not at page one of a fourteen-attachment email.

04:08.702 --> 04:11.609
One more thing — for the auditors.

04:11.659 --> 04:16.915
Every step this system took is written into a sealed logbook.

04:16.965 --> 04:24.221
Watch: we re-check it on the spot. Chain intact. Provable today, provable next year.

04:25.471 --> 04:28.739
Mark it reviewed... done. Next packet.

04:32.471 --> 04:37.809
AkamaiForms. Every submission, review ready. Your reviewers decide.

04:37.859 --> 04:40.623
The paperwork takes care of itself.
